10 a. Is taught by individuals licensed or approved to teach in early childhood
11 education by the education standards and practices board or approved to teach
12 in early childhood education by the education standards and practices board;
13 b. Follows four-year old program requirements approved by the department;
14 c. Is in compliance with all municipal and state health, fire, and safety requirements;
15 d. Limits enrollment to children who have reached the age of four years old before
16 August first in the year of enrollment, unless the child will be four years old before
17 December first and the school district determines, based on child development
18 factors, including development milestones, school readiness, and other individual
19 considerations, to allow a child to enroll based on a request;
20 e. Submits a nonrefundable fee of fifty dollars at the timewhen the application is
